### Screens & Features

#### OnboardingScreen
- Brief intro slides with illustrations (use icons as placeholders)
- Ask for monthly income (number), then guide to add expenses.
- CTA → “Start Planning”

#### PlanScreen (Tab 1)
- Top: Summary card: Income, Total Expenses, Surplus (with lucide icons: Wallet, Receipt, PiggyBank)
- Inputs/buttons to quickly adjust income or add/edit expenses
- Show **Daily** and **Weekly** recommended saving from surplus
- If a primary goal exists, show:
  - Time to reach (saving-only vs best-investing option)
  - Mini line chart comparing cumulative balances for 12–24 months
- Improvement Tips section (dynamic; see Tips below)

#### CompareScreen (Tab 2)
- User can pick: 
  - Goal amount (or choose from Goals)
  - Monthly contribution (default = current surplus)
  - Horizon selector (6, 12, 24, 36, 60, 120 months)
  - Instruments multi-select from config
- Render:
  - **Line chart**: growth over time for each selected instrument + saving-only
  - **Bar chart**: final amount at horizon, sorted desc
- A small table below with:
  - Instrument name, assumed annual rate, final value, gain vs saving-only
- CTA: “Set as Plan” to push chosen horizon + instrument mix to PlanScreen

#### GoalsScreen (Tab 3)
- List of goals (Card layout):
  - Title, Target amount, Optional target date
  - Badges: “Saving-only: X months”, “Investing: Y months”
- Add/Edit Goal modal (title, amount, target date optional)
- Tap a goal → GoalDetail:
  - Two charts: saving-only vs best-investment projection
  - Month-by-month schedule table
  - Share/Export (export as JSON via FileSystem)

#### LearnScreen (Tab 4)
Provide curated content cards (Q&A and checklists). Add at least 10 items:
- “What to check before investing?” (expense ratio, track record, benchmark, risk profile, tax, lock-in, liquidity)
- “PPF basics”
- “What is SIP?”
- “Gold ETF vs SGB”
- “FD vs Debt MF”
- “Risk vs Return”
- “Diversification 101”
- “How to pick an index fund”
- “What is RD and who should use it”
- “Tax considerations overview”
For each, provide a short, friendly explanation and a “Learn more” expandable section.

#### SettingsScreen (Tab 5)
- Edit default annual return rates per instrument
- Toggle dark mode / system theme
- Backup & Restore data (export/import JSON to device)
- Reset all data

### Data Model (TypeScript)
```ts
type Expense = {
  id: string;
  name: string; // Rent, EMI, etc.
  amount: number; // per month
  category?: 'Housing'|'EMI'|'Utilities'|'Groceries'|'Transport'|'Subscriptions'|'Other';
};

type Goal = {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  targetAmount: number;
  targetDate?: string; // ISO
  createdAt: string;
};

type InstrumentConfig = {
  id: string;
  name: string;           // "PPF", "Nifty Index", etc.
  annualRate: number;     // 0.071 for 7.1%
  compoundingPerYear: number; // default 12
  enabled: boolean;
  description?: string;
};

type AppState = {
  income: number;
  expenses: Expense[];
  goals: Goal[];
  instruments: InstrumentConfig[];
  theme: 'light' | 'dark' | 'system';
  primaryGoalId?: string;
};
